ğŸ”¹ Problem: Reverse String (Easy)
ğŸ”¹ Approach Used: Two Pointers

ğŸ’¡ Problem Explanation:
Given a string (or character array), reverse it in-place using minimal extra space.

ğŸ“ Solution Using Two Pointers
cpp
Copy
Edit
void reverseString(vector<char>& s) {
    int left = 0, right = s.size() - 1;
    while (left < right) {
        swap(s[left], s[right]);
        left++;
        right--;
    }
}
âœ… Efficient Approach:
âœ” Swaps first & last characters, moves pointers inward.
âœ” Time Complexity: O(N)
âœ” Space Complexity: O(1) (In-place reversal).
